  "body": "For discussion.\n\n### Description\nAs a staker, \nI want my node to ensure that its validators are unique on the network when it starts,\nso that I don't get slashed if another instance of the validator is running elsewhere. \n\nOne way this could be accomplished is to wait 2 (say) epochs before starting to attest and watch the network. If any attestations are seen from validators I believe I own, this should trigger the kill-switch.\n\nIt should be optional (default, but able to override?) as staking services are unlikely to want to miss epochs.\n\nA small number of instances of slashing on mainnet may have been avoidable with such a mechanism. Current folklore in the staking community is to wait at least two epochs after stopping a node before restarting; this mechanism would effectively automate that.\n\n- [x] Add doppelganger detection activation flag\n- [x] Add validators liveness check to Validator API Channel\n- [x] Add doppelganger detection to Validator Client Service\n- [x] Handle the validators added via the keymanager API\n- [x] Add tests\n\n@mehdi-aouadi [notes](https://hackmd.io/St0_OdKwROKSgYzGJhaZMw?view)",
